<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[151,869,1558,1584]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">The group comprises 4 species. It is characterised as follows:</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[199,1009,1598,1624]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">­ ground colour of forewing blackish brown with violet tint (apo.);</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[199,1031,1638,1664]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">­ antemedial and upper half of subterminal lines well marked, black;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[199,699,1678,1704]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">­ reniform stigma prominent, yellowish;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[199,674,1718,1744]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">­ hindwing with indistinct discal spot;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[199,526,1758,1784]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">­ saccus short, triangular;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[199,504,1798,1824]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">­ tergite inconspicuous;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[199,1215,1838,1864]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">­ phallus broadest at ductus ejaculatorius, curved subapically, tapered towards apex;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[199,801,1878,1904]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">­ vesica most often with small triangular cornuti;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1368,1558,1944]" box="[199,1368,1918,1944]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">­ ductus bursae very long, cylindrical, membranous; medially with coil close to ductus seminalis.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
